Table: pirate_treasure
{1d6 * 500} pieces of eight
a chest of {2d10 * 100} doubloons and [@pirate_gem]
the [|cursed|legendary|enchanted|stolen] [|compass|blade|map|crown] of [@pirate_name]
\a [|jade|ruby|sapphire|pearl] idol worth {1d4 * 1000} gold

Table: pirate_gem
a flawless [|ruby|emerald|sapphire|diamond]
{1d6} [|garnets|opals|moonstones|topazes]

Table: pirate_complication
5:a naval frigate is in pursuit
the first mate has betrayed the crew
the charts are forged — destination unknown
[{1d3}] stowaways are hiding below decks
the treasure is cursed
a rival captain is hunting the same prize

// ================================================================
// ----------------------------------------------------------------
//  UTILITY TABLES — shared across themes
// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// ================================================================

Table: world_name
Aethoria
Valdremoor
The Shattered Reach
Ironmere
Deepfen
Crestholm
The Pale Expanse
Valdris

// ================================================================
// ================================================================
//  STANDALONE FEATURE DEMOS
//  These tables are not called from the main oracle.
//  To test them: change the main table's first item to call [@demo_X]
// ================================================================
// ================================================================

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// DEMO: All filters
// ----------------------------------------------------------------
Table: demo_filters
// lower, upper, proper
[@world_name >> lower]  ← lower\n&
[@world_name >> upper]  ← upper\n&
[@world_name >> proper] ← proper\n&
// reverse, left, right, substr
[Aethoria >> reverse]   ← reverse\n&
[Aethoria >> left 4]    ← left 4\n&
[Aethoria >> right 3]   ← right 3\n&
[Aethoria >> substr 3 4] ← substr 3 4\n&
// at (find position of substring)
[abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz >> at r] ← at r (position of r)\n&
// replace
[You see orcs attacking >> replace /orcs/ancient dragons/] ← replace\n&
// plusminus (numeric modifier formatting)
[{1d40 - 20} >> +-]  ← +- format\n&
// sort and implode on multiple results
[@3 pirate_skills >> sort >> implode] ← 3 skills sorted+joined\n&
// bold, italic, underline (HTML mode)
[DANGER >> bold]\n&
[whispered secret >> italic]\n&
[important >> underline]\n&
// trim
[   trimmed   >> trim] ← trim\n&
// length
[Sparkwyrd >> length] ← length

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// DEMO: each filter — process each result through a table
// ----------------------------------------------------------------
Table: demo_each
[!4 pirate_skills >> each skill_wrap >> implode]

Table: skill_wrap
// {$1} receives each skill name in turn
<b>{$1}</b> (lvl {1d6})

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// DEMO: eachchar filter — process each character through a table
// ----------------------------------------------------------------
Table: demo_eachchar
[ORACLE >> eachchar dot_each]

Table: dot_each
// {$1} = one character at a time
{$1}.

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// DEMO: with params — pass arguments to a sub-table
// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// Call: [@stat_block]
Table: stat_block
[@make_stat with Strength, {3d6}]\n&
[@make_stat with Dexterity, {3d6}]\n&
[@make_stat with Constitution, {3d6}]\n&
[@make_stat with Intelligence, {3d6}]\n&
[@make_stat with Wisdom, {3d6}]\n&
[@make_stat with Charisma, {3d6}]

// Feature: {$1} = first param (stat name), {$2} = second (value)
//          inline math + plusminus filter
Table: make_stat
{$1}: {$2}  (mod: [{$2} - 10 >> +-])

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// DEMO: inline variable assignment
// ----------------------------------------------------------------
Table: demo_assign
// {var=expr}: evaluate expression, assign to var, AND output result
Roll was: {myroll=1d20}\n&
// {var==expr}: evaluate, assign, but do NOT output
{mymod=={myroll} - 10}&
Modifier: [{mymod} >> +-]\n&
// [@var=table]: roll on table, assign, AND output
[@picked=fantasy_item] — stored.\n&
// Use the stored value again (no re-roll):
You found it again: {picked}\n&
// [@var==table]: roll and assign silently
[@picked==pirate_gem]&
// Output later:
Hidden gem: {picked}

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// DEMO: special characters
// ----------------------------------------------------------------
Table: demo_special
// \n = newline in output
Line one\nLine two\nLine three\n&
// \t = tab character
Name:\tAldric Stonehammer\n&
// \z = explicit empty string (item can be blank without being skipped)
Before\z After (no gap, \z is empty)\n&
// \_ = forced space (useful in filter arguments)
Three\_spaces: [|A|B|C] \_\_\_ [|X|Y|Z]\n&
// \a = insert "a" or "an" based on next letter
\a ancient ruin, \a elf, \a dragon, \a orc, \a iron door\n&
// Line continuation & : next line is part of same item
This is a very long item that spans &
multiple lines in the source file &
but appears as a single line in output.

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// DEMO: line continuation for complex items
// ----------------------------------------------------------------
Table: demo_prophecy
// The & at line end joins lines without a line break
When the [|twin moons|black sun|silver comet] &
rises over the [@location_adj] mountains of {@world}, &
a {lucky_die}-day reckoning shall begin — &
seek the [@fantasy_item] before [@fantasy_monster >> proper] &
claims the throne of [@world_name].

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// DEMO: \z as explicit empty item (one entry out of many is blank)
// ----------------------------------------------------------------
Table: magic_bonus
5:\z
2:+1 Magic
1:+2 Magic

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// DEMO: nesting — table name from variable, count from dice
// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// [@{var}] uses a variable as the table name
// [@{NdN} table] uses a dice roll as the repeat count
Table: demo_nesting
// Table name from variable (theme was set in oracle)
Best class for theme: [@best_{theme}_class]\n&
// Random number of sub-table rolls
Loot: [@{1d3} fantasy_item >> implode]

Table: best_fantasy_class
Fighter or Wizard
Table: best_steampunk_class
Engineer or Inspector
Table: best_pirate_class
Rogue or Navigator

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// DEMO: Default: for tables that might miss
// ----------------------------------------------------------------
Table: demo_default_lookup
Type: Lookup
Roll: 1d12
Default: A common soldier
1-2:A lone scout
3-5:A patrol of three
6-8:A full squad
9-10:An elite unit
11:A war mage
12:The commander herself

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// DEMO: multiple repetitions + implode separator
// ----------------------------------------------------------------
Table: demo_multi
[@5 world_name >> implode  |  ]

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// DEMO: [when not] conditional — fires when condition is FALSE
// ----------------------------------------------------------------
Table: demo_when_not
Set: val = {1d10}
Value: {val}\n&
[when not]{val} > 5[do]Low roll — you struggle.[end]&
[when]{val} > 5[do]High roll — you succeed![end]
